    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>E-ZPASS CAMERAS REDUCED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Karen Demasters</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Jersey Turnpike Authority decides to reduce number of cameras mounted to catch big trucks trying to cheat E-ZPass toll collection system along southern ends of New Jersey Turnpike and Garden State Parkway, saving about $2 million (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The number of cameras that will be mounted to catch big trucks trying to cheat the E-ZPass toll collection system on the turnpike and parkway has been reduced to 101 from 380. The New Jersey Turnpike Authority, which is overseeing E-ZPass installation, said last week that it decided to order fewer cameras because few trucks use the southern end of the roads. The change saves $5 million of the $7 million originally budgeted for the cameras.</p>
        <p>Karen DeMasters</p>
      </block>
